node.text: On this day in 1986, Douglas Adams explained how the idea for The Hitchhiker’s Guide to the Galaxy came to him while lying drunk in a field in Innsburck. For those of us who enjoy writing, or creating more generally, it's always inspiring to learn what inspires the best. Most of the time it's not so planned. Going back to the quote I shared on the page yesterday, it tends to be more about having the courage and drive to connect dots. - video via @bbc_archive
